<section class="section-block faq-block">
	<h2>Starter FAQ copy</h2>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Is VoiceTel only for developers?</summary>
		<p>No. VoiceTel serves developers, telecom engineers, operators, and business buyers across programmable voice, messaging, SIP trunking, numbers, hosted PBX, and phone applications.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Can I migrate a compatible Twilio voice app?</summary>
		<p>Yes, if the app stays inside the supported VoiceML-compatible voice surface. Check compatibility and run test calls before cutover.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Are VoiceTel rates public?</summary>
		<p>VoiceTel publishes approved public rates when available. Account-specific rates are labeled custom or handled through sales.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Do calculator inputs leave the browser?</summary>
		<p>No. The calculator states that usage inputs remain client-side.</p>
	</details>
	<details class="faq-item">
		<summary>Does VoiceTel support emergency calling?</summary>
		<p>Emergency-service availability and limitations depend on number type, service address, product configuration, and signed terms. The legal page and service terms explain those limitations.</p>
	</details>
</section>
